  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with comprehensive legal frameworks designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key legal aspects:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- International monetary cooperation standards\n\n2. Typical Legal Components\n- Definition of money laundering offenses\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Customer due diligence regulations\n- Suspicious transaction monitoring\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n3. Key Legislation Examples\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- EU Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset confiscation\n- Professional disqualification\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Regular reporting to financial authorities\n\n6. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have varying specific regulations\n- Increasing global coordination and standardization\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent financial crimes and maintain economic integrity.",
